\begin_layout Standard
Suppose 
\begin_inset Formula $\sqrt{2}$
\end_inset

 were rational.
 Then there would exist 
\begin_inset Formula $a,b\in\mathbb{Z}$
\end_inset

 st 
\begin_inset Formula $b\neq0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{a}{b}$
\end_inset

 is fully reduced.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\sqrt{2}=\frac{a}{b}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
2=\frac{a^{2}}{b^{2}}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
2b^{2}=a^{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As 
\begin_inset Formula $a,b$
\end_inset

 are integers, this implies 
\begin_inset Formula $a^{2}$
\end_inset

 is divisible by 
\begin_inset Formula $2$
\end_inset

, as is 
\begin_inset Formula $a$
\end_inset

.
 In other words, 
\begin_inset Formula $a=2c$
\end_inset

 for some 
\begin_inset Formula $c\in\mathbb{Z}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
2b^{2}=\left(2c\right)^{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
2b^{2}=4c^{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
b^{2}=2c^{2}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This implies 
\begin_inset Formula $b^{2}$
\end_inset

 is also divisible by 
\begin_inset Formula $2$
\end_inset

 and therefore 
\begin_inset Formula $b$
\end_inset

 is as well.
 As 
\begin_inset Formula $a,b$
\end_inset

 are both divisible by 
\begin_inset Formula $2$
\end_inset

, this contradicts our earlier assumption that 
\begin_inset Formula $\frac{a}{b}$
\end_inset

 is fully simplified! Thus to avoid contradiction, we must allow 
\begin_inset Formula $\sqrt{2}$
\end_inset

